.Dd March 29, 2026
.Dt KATADM 8
.Os Kayoko
.Sh NAME
.Nm katadm
.Nd administrative tool for the Kernel Access Table
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm load | clear | status | list
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility manages the security rules within the KAT kernel module. 
It translates human-readable configurations into bitmasks and uploads them to
.Pa /dev/kat .
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Cm load
Parses
.Pa /etc/kat.conf ,
clears the existing kernel table, and uploads new rules.
.It Cm clear
Flushes all rules from the kernel's in-memory table, effectively 
reverting the system to default kernel security.
.It Cm status
Displays a summary of the number of active rules currently enforced.
.It Cm list
Provides a formatted table of all active rules, including UIDs, 
hexadecimal privilege masks, and target paths.
.El
.Sh CONFIGURATION SYNTAX
Rules in
.Pa /etc/kat.conf
follow a three-column format:
.Pp
.Dl "IDENTITY    PATH    PRIVILEGE"
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Sy IDENTITY
Can be a username, a numeric UID, or a group name prefixed with 
.Sq % .
Groups are expanded to their constituent members at load time.
.It Sy PATH
The absolute path to a binary. Use 
.Sq * for a global rule that applies regardless of the executed binary.
.It Sy PRIVILEGE
A pipe-separated list of keywords (e.g., 
.Li sys.reboot|net.bind ) .
If prefixed with 
.Sq ! ,
the rule becomes a 
.Em restriction 
rather than an allowance.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/etc/kat.conf" -compact
.It Pa /etc/kat.conf
The default policy file. Supports 
.Li -- 
style comments.
.It Pa /dev/kat
The character device interface for kernel communication.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kat 1 ,
.Xr kat 4
